# React Three Fiber Patterns

- Use R3F declarative JSX (`<mesh>`, `<boxGeometry>`) — avoid imperative `new THREE.Mesh()` in render
- `useFrame` callbacks must multiply by `delta` for frame-rate independence
- Memoize expensive geometry/material with `useMemo` — never create them inline in JSX
- Dispose geometries and materials in cleanup (`useEffect` return) when dynamically created
- Use `drei` helpers first: `<Html>`, `<Text>`, `<Float>`, `<RoundedBox>`, etc.
- `<Html>` components need `transform` and `occlude` props for proper 3D integration
- Group related meshes with `<group>` and apply transforms at the group level
- Spring animations via `@react-spring/three` — use `animated.group` or `animated.mesh`
- Keep the R3F `<Canvas>` in a client component; page-level components can be server components
- Performance: use `<Instances>` for repeated geometry, limit draw calls
